{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596061","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596061"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15389"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15389"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.67,0.05,0.29,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8080"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63725"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8080","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8080"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15389"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49164"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1095"},{"type":"tags","id":"1449"},{"type":"tags","id":"3444"},{"type":"tags","id":"3696"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8133"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19609"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19614"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20885"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63725","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63725"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA previously well 29-year-old woman presents with a three month history of persistent diarrhoea and lower abdominal pain. The physical examination is unremarkable. The clinician is reasonably certain that the patient has inflammatory bowel disease.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following would be the most appropriate diagnostic investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Colonoscopy with biopsy","Computed tomography enterography","Faecal calprotectin measurement","Magnetic resonance enterography","Wireless capsule endoscopy"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColonoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E with biopsy is the gold standard diagnostic test for inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) as it allows direct visualisation of the colonic mucosa and collection of tissue samples for histological examination. This helps establish the diagnosis and differentiate between ulcerative colitis and Crohn disease based on the distribution and appearance of lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFaecal calprotectin\u003C/strong\u003E is a useful screening tool and can help monitor disease activity, but cannot definitively diagnose IBD. \u003Cstrong\u003EComputed tomography enterography\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Emagnetic resonance enterography\u003C/strong\u003E are complementary imaging techniques that assess small bowel involvement and complications but cannot replace endoscopic evaluation. They are key investigations in the long-term follow up of patients with IBD.  \u003Cstrong\u003EWireless capsule endoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E can visualise the small intestine but has limited utility as a first-line diagnostic tool and is contraindicated if strictures are present.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Colonoscopy with biopsy is the gold standard test for diagnosing inflammatory bowel disease as it allows direct visualization and tissue sampling.","Endoscopic evaluation helps differentiate between ulcerative colitis and Crohn disease based on distribution and appearance of lesions."],"references":["McDowell C, Farooq U, Haseeb M. Inflammatory Bowel Disease. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262182.","Fakhoury M, Negrulj R, Mooranian A, Al-Salami H. Inflammatory bowel disease: clinical aspects and treatments. J Inflamm Res. 2014 Jun 23;7:113-20. doi: 10.2147/JIR.S65979. PMID: 25075198; PMCID: PMC4106026.","Tavakoli P, Vollmer-Conna U, Hadzi-Pavlovic D, Grimm MC. A Review of Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A Model of Microbial, Immune and Neuropsychological Integration. Public Health Rev. 2021 May 5;42:1603990. doi: 10.3389/phrs.2021.1603990. PMID: 34692176; PMCID: PMC8386758.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49164"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15389"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49164","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49164"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-22T12:13:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T12:13:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8080"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63725"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d